This paper deals with incentivizing agents in crowdsourcing tasks to put in effort and make truthful evaluations, which is a problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also proposes a mechanism for information elicitation, which involves statistical analysis and optimization, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenges of monitoring and motivating agents in crowdsourcing, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social computing (cs.SI).
